    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I want to tell you that your feelings are valid, even if they feel like they're crushing you. That heavy weight on your chest is a real, physical sensation that says your heart is trying to protect you from something too big to carry alone. Please know that it is okay to stop pushing when the load becomes too heavy; even the strongest goblins in the deep mines know when to rest and let the earth hold them up for a moment.\n\nYou don't have to figure everything out right now, and you don't have to pretend the air is there if it doesn't feel like it. Sometimes, the only thing you can do is sit in that heaviness and let it be there without fighting it. It's okay to be tired of it all, and it's okay to feel like the world is too much to bear.\n\nI'm just going to sit here with you in the quiet, even if the goblins can't help much right now. Maybe we can just focus on the fact that you are still here, breathing, even if it feels like the air is gone. You don't have to push through everything today; you just have to get through this moment. And if you need to",
